032@SuppressWarnings({
033    "PMD.DataClass",
034    "PMD.FieldNamingConventions"
035})
036@MetaschemaAssembly(
037    formalName = "Allowed Values Constraint",
038    name = "flag-allowed-values",
039    moduleClass = MetaschemaModelModule.class)
040public class FlagAllowedValues implements IBoundObject, IConstraintBase {
041  private final IMetaschemaData __metaschemaData;
042
043  @BoundFlag(
044      formalName = "Constraint Identifier",
045      name = "id",
046      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class)
047  private String _id;
048
049  @BoundFlag(
050      formalName = "Constraint Severity Level",
051      name = "level",
052      defaultValue = "ERROR",
053      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
054      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR, values = {
055          @AllowedValue(value = "CRITICAL",
056              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a serious fault in the content that will prevent typical use of the content."),
057          @AllowedValue(value = "ERROR",
058              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a fault in the content. This may include issues around compatibility, integrity, consistency, etc."),
059          @AllowedValue(value = "WARNING",
060              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a potential issue with the content."),
061          @AllowedValue(value = "INFORMATIONAL",
062              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a point of interest."),
063          @AllowedValue(value = "DEBUG",
064              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a fault in the content that may warrant review by a developer when performing model or tool development.") })))
065  private String _level;
066
067  @BoundFlag(
068      formalName = "Allow Non-Enumerated Values?",
069      name = "allow-other",
070      defaultValue = "no",
071      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
072      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR,
073          values = { @AllowedValue(value = "no", description = ""), @AllowedValue(value = "yes", description = "") })))
074  private String _allowOther;
075
076  /**
077   * "Determines if the given enumerated values may be extended by other allowed
078   * value constraints."
079   */
080  @BoundFlag(
081      formalName = "Allow Extension?",
082      description = "Determines if the given enumerated values may be extended by other allowed value constraints.",
083      name = "extensible",
084      defaultValue = "external",
085      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
086      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR,
087          values = {
088              @AllowedValue(value = "model", description = "Can be extended by constraints within the same module."),
089              @AllowedValue(value = "external", description = "Can be extended by external constraints."),
090              @AllowedValue(value = "none", description = "Cannot be extended.") })))
091  private String _extensible;
092
093  @BoundField(
094      formalName = "Formal Name",
095      description = "A formal name for the data construct, to be presented in documentation.",
096      useName = "formal-name")
097  private String _formalName;
098
099  @BoundField(
100      formalName = "Description",
101      description = "A short description of the data construct's purpose, describing the constructs semantics.",
102      useName = "description",
103      typeAdapter = MarkupLineAdapter.class)
104  private MarkupLine _description;
105
106  @BoundAssembly(
107      formalName = "Property",
108      useName = "prop",
109      maxOccurs = -1,
110      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "props", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
111  private List<Property> _props;
112
113  @BoundField(
114      formalName = "Allowed Value Enumeration",
115      useName = "enum",
116      minOccurs = 1,
117      maxOccurs = -1,
118      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "enums", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
119  private List<ConstraintValueEnum> _enums;
120
121  @BoundField(
122      formalName = "Remarks",
123      description = "Any explanatory or helpful information to be provided about the remarks parent.",
124      useName = "remarks")
125  private Remarks _remarks;

128    this(null);
129  }

146    _id = value;
147  }

152  }

155    _level = value;
156  }
157
158  public String getAllowOther() {
159    return _allowOther;
160  }
161
162  public void setAllowOther(String value) {
163    _allowOther = value;
164  }
165
166  public String getExtensible() {
167    return _extensible;
168  }
169
170  public void setExtensible(String value) {
171    _extensible = value;
172  }
173
174  @Override
175  public String getFormalName() {
176    return _formalName;
177  }
178
179  public void setFormalName(String value) {
180    _formalName = value;
181  }
182
183  @Override
184  public MarkupLine getDescription() {
185    return _description;
186  }
187
188  public void setDescription(MarkupLine value) {
189    _description = value;
190  }
191
192  @Override
193  public List<Property> getProps() {
194    return _props;
195  }
196
197  public void setProps(List<Property> value) {
198    _props = value;
199  }
200
201  /**
202   * Add a new {@link Property} item to the underlying collection.
203   *
204   * @param item
205   *          the item to add
206   * @return {@code true}
207   */
208  public boolean addProp(Property item) {
209    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
210    if (_props == null) {
211      _props = new LinkedList<>();
212    }
213    return _props.add(value);
214  }
215
216  /**
217   * Remove the first matching {@link Property} item from the underlying
218   * collection.
219   *
220   * @param item
221   *          the item to remove
222   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
223   */
224  public boolean removeProp(Property item) {
225    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
226    return _props != null && _props.remove(value);
227  }
228
229  public List<ConstraintValueEnum> getEnums() {
230    return _enums;
231  }
232
233  public void setEnums(List<ConstraintValueEnum> value) {
234    _enums = value;
235  }
236
237  /**
238   * Add a new {@link ConstraintValueEnum} item to the underlying collection.
239   *
240   * @param item
241   *          the item to add
242   * @return {@code true}
243   */
244  public boolean addEnum(ConstraintValueEnum item) {
245    ConstraintValueEnum value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
246    if (_enums == null) {
247      _enums = new LinkedList<>();
248    }
249    return _enums.add(value);
250  }
251
252  /**
253   * Remove the first matching {@link ConstraintValueEnum} item from the
254   * underlying collection.
255   *
256   * @param item
257   *          the item to remove
258   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
259   */
260  public boolean removeEnum(ConstraintValueEnum item) {
261    ConstraintValueEnum value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
262    return _enums != null && _enums.remove(value);
263  }
264
265  @Override
266  public Remarks getRemarks() {
267    return _remarks;
268  }
269
270  public void setRemarks(Remarks value) {
271    _remarks = value;
272  }
273
274  @Override
275  public String toString() {
276    return new ReflectionToStringBuilder(this, ToStringStyle.MULTI_LINE_STYLE).toString();
277  }
